title: Carey Mulligan welcomes first child
text:
Carey Mulligan well-suited for 'Great Gatsby' role 
Actress Carey Mulligan has confirmed rumours she is a first-time mom after giving birth to a baby girl. 
The Great Gatsby star delivered her first child with her rocker husband Marcus Mumford last month. She has not made her daughter's name public. 
Mulligan was rumoured to be pregnant earlier this year but she did not confirm the report and was not pictured sporting a baby bump. 
Earlier this week, she attended the London premiere of her new movie Suffragette and sparked speculation she had given birth as she was clearly not with-child. 
Now the actress has finally ended the rumours and confirmed she is a new mother. 
Filming an interview with U.K. talk show host Graham Norton on Thursday evening, Mulligan said, "Yep. It is a girl and she's three weeks old." 
The interview is due to air in the U.K. on Friday. Sponsored Links
